PHOTO: Building collapsed at 50, Kakawa Lagos Island, four kilometres away from Ita-Faji where school children were recently killed in the same incident. Another building has collapsed in Lagos, a few weeks after 20 persons were confirmed killed in a similar accident. The scene of the latest collapse at 50, Kakawa on Lagos Island, is less than four kilometres from Ita Faji where school children were among those that died. “Preliminary investigation revealed that the building had been noticed to be defective and all occupants had been evacuated from the building,” Lagos State Government said on Monday. The government said no one died in the accident.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .